article.headline: Indiana 88, Florida Gulf Coast 60
article.story: BLOOMINGTON, Ind. -- Christian Watford scored 24 points and Jordan Hulls had 18, leading Indiana to an 88-60 win over Florida Gulf Coast in the season-opener for both teams Friday night. Indiana (1-0) has now won 13 straight season-openers and 26 consecutive home openers. The Eagles (0-1) were led by Anthony Banks, who had 16 points, but dropped to 1-10 all-time against BCS schools and 0-4 all-time against the Big Ten. Florida Gulf Coast hung around for a while, closing to nine early in the second half and getting within 56-44 with 15:50 to go. But Watford answered with six straight points and Indiana never let the Eagles get close again. Indiana connected on 14 of 28 shots from 3-point range, and Watford finished with five rebounds and four assists.
